rComments: Professor Fitzgibbon is a great prof who really cares about her students. She marks tough but fair and is always wiling to explain her reasoning. TRN 151 covered a wide variety of topics, some of which are quite boring, but she does her best to make it interesting and exciting. 10/10 would recommend.

rComments: Joy is hands down the greatest professor I ever had at U of T. She teaches thoughtful, interesting and relevant lectures - I always looked forward to attending her classes. She truly cares about not only the success of her students, but their wellbeing, too. She is always accessible, quick to help, and all around amazing. Take a course with her!

My favorite professor so far! Passionate and kind. Goes out of her way to help students. While her course is definitely challenging, she grades very fairly. Worth it to take TrinOne just to have her as a prof!

Among the best professors I've ever had the pleasure of knowing. She is readily accessible and clearly cares about her students. Even if global health isn't your direct passion, Fitzgibbon will manage to keep you invested in what she has to say. I would highly recommend!

Indeed the course (TRN151) was pretty challenging for first-years, but trust me it benefits you in all kinds of aspects imaginable. The prof was extremely approachable and helpful too. She is always there for you when you need help. She managed to make complex topics very accessable to students. Her page-long response to papers truly helps a lot.

Professor Fitzgibbon is an amazing professor like no other. She cares deeply about students, both academically and personally. Her TRN151 course is challenging, but definitely worth it.  To do well, one must think critically about the issues being presented. Fortunately, there is must leeway to choose topics that interest you to focus on.

Joy is the best prof I have ever had, and probably will ever have. She creates super interesting lectures, encourages awesome discussions, and truly engages students. She's constantly making time to help students, and is awesome to talk to about anything. If you can take a course with her, DO IT!
joy is one of the best profs at uoft! she really cares about her students, and sets up a really interesting course!

Joy Fitzgibbon was an absolute pleasure to learn from this year. She made classes bearable, was a fall marker and offered excessive office hour opportunities for students to ask questions and advice. I would take any course taught by Professor Fitzgibbon, simply because she is so wonderful and is excellent at her craft.
